channel.title: People can't log in to my server
channel.description:
Oh yeah, I'm gonna tell this fastly:
I had working moaprscape server, like 6 months ago. But now people can't log on? People could do that before. I've "updated" ip, and I think i have portforwarded right.
What should I do?
Thanks :|

item.dc:creator: @akijamake akijamake
item.description:
@akijamake wrote:

[quote=“tw33zy, post:2, topic:270933”]Em, make sure your firewall isn’t blocking anything, also make sure you’ve got a static ip, not dynamic, a static ip adress changed it self quite frequently, meaning you have to portforward again, follow the TuTs on;

www.portforward.com

Thanks

I just noticed that my Firewall was blocking the port 43594
~Johno[/quote]
